  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2cbaeec8dbe84e069925173ac3a6210b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Dlg_Ruins_Guardian_Riddle
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ElementalAlchemist.Dialogue.DialogueData
  _speaker: Ruins Guardian
  _lines:
  - You stand among the bones of an age that begged never to die. They chased a single prize, and it unmade every one of them.
  - Wed the flawless jewel the deep weeps under unbearable weight to the golden draught that holds death at the door. Together they make that prize.
  - The old totems still remember how each is wrought, if you stop to listen. Bring me the prize, and the Fragment of Soul is yours.
